<title>ISRAEL: Koor raises Tadiran stake.</title>
<headline>Koor raises Tadiran stake.</headline>
<dateline>TEL AVIV 1997-03-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Koor Industries Ltd purchased 40,000 shares in Tadiran Ltd at 86.17 shekels each in an off-the-floor transaction on Monday, the company announced to the Tel Aviv bourse on Tuesday.</p>
<p>Koor, which now owns 12,470,029 shares in Tadiran, raised its total stake in Israel's largest electronics company by 0.2 percent to 63.677 percent.</p>
<p>The purchase was part of Koor's strategy of enlarging its holdings in its core businesses.</p>
<p>Both Koor and Tadiran also trade on the New York Stock Exchange.</p>
<p>($1 = 3.67 shekels)</p>
<p>-Tel Aviv newsroom, 972-3-537-2211</p>
